Greek Debt Delay Only Possible With Banks, Schaeuble Tells Bild

-- B y   S h e e n a g h   M a t t h e w s
-- 
2011-05-22T12:30:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-22/greek-debt-delay-only-possible-with-banks-schaeuble-tells-bild.html
German Finance Minister  Wolfgang Schaeuble  said the maturities of Greek government debt could
only be extended if private creditors such as banks took part
and the  International Monetary Fund  and the  European Central
Bank  agreed, according to  Bild am Sonntag .  Schaeuble also said that there are no grounds for fear of
inflation as the euro and prices will remain stable, the German
newspaper reported, citing an interview with the minister.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
